Below is an instruction that describes a task. Write a response that appropriately completes the request.

### Instruction:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:

This command will create a new SSH key pair and use it to establish an SSH connection between the local machine and a remote server at IP address 25900. The "user" variable is set to point to the server at ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com.
